## Important distinction for roles

This mapping:

```java
.map(
    PersonSalesPointRelationshipEntity::
        getRelationshipType
)
```

is correct only when database relationship types represent application roles, such as:

```text
SELLER
DEALER
ZONE_MANAGER
```

If `relationshipType` represents employment relationships rather than authorization roles, do not use it for `response.roles`. In that case, return an empty list until a proper role table or repository exists:

```java
response.setRoles(List.of());
```

Based on the current database model shown, roles can safely be derived only from `relationshipType`; dealer and zone-manager identities cannot yet be derived reliably.

## Cleaner version using helper methods

To keep `mapToResponse(...)` smaller, extract the database mapping:

```java
private List<SalesPointResponse> mapSalesPoints(
        List<PersonSalesPointRelationshipEntity> relationships
) {
    return relationships.stream()
            .map(this::mapSalesPoint)
            .toList();
}

private SalesPointResponse mapSalesPoint(
        PersonSalesPointRelationshipEntity relationship
) {
    String salesPointId = relationship.getSalesPointId();

    SalesPointEntity salesPoint =
            salesPointRepository
                    .findBySalesPointId(salesPointId)
                    .orElseThrow(
                            () -> new SalesPointNotFoundException(
                                    salesPointId
                            )
                    );

    return new SalesPointResponse(
            salesPoint.getSalesPointId(),
            salesPoint.getLabel(),
            relationship.getOrgUnitId()
    );
}

private List<String> mapRoles(
        List<PersonSalesPointRelationshipEntity> relationships
) {
    return relationships.stream()
            .map(
                    PersonSalesPointRelationshipEntity::
                            getRelationshipType
            )
            .filter(Objects::nonNull)
            .map(String::trim)
            .filter(role -> !role.isEmpty())
            .distinct()
            .toList();
}
```

